  "highlights": [
    "The clean-start campaign validated 28q as a repeatable frontier for GHZ on CPU/double, GPU/double, and GPU/single.",
    "The GPU/double GHZ slice was extended with a dedicated 29q run, which failed during warmup and confirmed 28q as the practical stable ceiling for that slice.",
    "CPU/double random and GPU/single trotter were the most restrictive workloads in this campaign, stabilizing only up to 20q.",
    "The sustained multi-slice batch run is still useful as an endurance signal, but it underreports the frontier because WSL degrades under long continuous stress."
